<h1>Courting Disaster: Dec. 7, 2012</h1>
<h2 class="postcat_courting_disaster postauthor_Guigar">in <a href="/search/index.html?search=forums;q=category%3A%22Courting%20Disaster%22;by=date">Courting Disaster</a> by <a href="/users/Guigar/">Guigar</a></h2>
<h3 class="date">Friday, December 07, 2012 - 12:00 AM</h3>
<div class="content">
    <a href="http://www.courting-disaster.com"><img src="/images/blogart/cd20121208_thumb.jpg" hspace="20" align="right"></a> <br><br>Courting Disaster is my weekly relationship-advice comic where a reader asks a question, and <b>you</b> give the advice.<br><br>

<i>A reader writes...</i></font><br><br>

Q. <b>After my girlfriend and I broke up about 3 days ago, a girl I've known since sophomore year in high school gave me a BJ to get me to stop being gloomy.  Now my ex wants to get back together. What should I do?</b><br><br><br>

<i>Don't answer here</i>... go to the <a href="http://www.courting-disaster.com">Courting Disaster site to offer your advice.</a><br><br>

<a href="http://www.bloomingfaeries.com/?page_id=3295"><img src="/images/blogart/BF0002-Molly_icon.jpeg" align="left" hspace="20"></a><h1>William I. Guam on Blooming Faeries...</h1>



<br>

And while we're in the NSFW mindset... If you're a fan of Jaycee Knight's <a href="http://www.bloomingfaeries.com">Blooming Faeries</a> (NSFW), you may have noticed a new, members-only comic by William I. Guam. Jaycee has asked me to let you know that interested Courting Disaster readers can check this new comic out under a <a href="http://www.bloomingfaeries.com/?page_id=3295">special membership offer</a> at Blooming Faeries.
</div>
